explains: v. 使凌乱；胡乱地填满（clutter 的过去式和过去分词）
wordGroup: sea clutter 海面回波；海面干扰

sentences.en: The vehicles cluttered up the parking lot.
The yards are overgrown and cluttered with trash.
sentences.cn: 院子杂草丛生，堆满了垃圾。

sentences.en: She ushered her callers into a cluttered living room.
sentences.cn: 她把来客们带到一间杂乱的客厅。
